overview: "The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetics
  of their sleep questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The agent
  conducted a comprehensive review, identifying issues with the color palette,
  typography, spacing, form elements, and overall visual interest. The approach
  involved a multi-step implementation: first, a complete overhaul of the global
  color palette to a calming, sleep-themed design. This was followed by
  extensive styling updates to the main QuestionnaireForm layout, including a
  redesigned progress indicator and card headers with subtle patterns. The
  IntroSection was transformed into a more engaging welcome experience with
  feature cards and improved alerts. Crucially, all core UI components like
  Checkbox, RadioGroup, Slider, and Progress were refined for a modern, polished
  look. Finally, the agent systematically applied these new styling principles
  to all questionnaire sections, replacing old gray-boxed groupings with
  visually appealing, themed cards, and updated the ReportSection for a cohesive
  final presentation. The goal was to move the app from a functional but plain
  interface to a professional, trustworthy, and aesthetically pleasing sleep
  health application."
